---
// Matches gatsby's minimal 404 (no site chrome, no <title>).
// parity/gatsby-build/404/index.html has no <title> element at all -- the old NotFoundPage
// component never rendered a Helmet/SEO block, so react-helmet never injected one and
// gatsby's default html.js doesn't supply a fallback title. Confirmed by grepping the
// captured build for <title (attribute-aware, e.g. data-react-helmet) -- zero matches.
//
// Gatsby *did* still inject the typography.js stylesheet + Google Fonts link into the 404 head,
// so its bare `<h1>Page Not Found</h1>` rendered in the sans-serif heading font (Source Sans Pro,
// weight 600). It did NOT pick up globals.css, whose `html { font-size: 112.5% }` (125% >=1240px)
// bumps the fluid root every normal page uses -- so gatsby's 404 root stayed at typography's base
// 16px, making its h1 a true 2rem = 32px, smaller than the 36-40px it is on chrome-bearing pages.
// Import ONLY typography.css to reproduce that exactly (verified: baseline 404 heading bbox is
// ~13% smaller than the fluid-root size). No globals/vars/viewport-units/gatsby-image: the 404 has
// nothing but the heading, and pulling in the fluid root would oversize it.
import "../styles/typography.css";
---
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link
      href="//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Source+Sans+Pro:400,600,700|Noto+Serif:400"
      rel="stylesheet"
      type="text/css"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>Page Not Found</h1>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
